 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.446","title":"[audit][stream] Fresh-eyes audit of src/stream/fuse.rs","description":"Bounded audit child under asupersync-1qfd0. Deeply inspect src/stream/fuse.rs for exhaustion latching, terminal repoll fail-closed behavior, pending-after-completion edges, and interaction with the wrapped stream. Fix any concrete bug found, add targeted regression tests, validate with rch-backed checks/tests for the touched surface, and append an audit_index entry when complete.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"OrangeRiver","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:45:55.829089930Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T03:49:51.957806620Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T03:49:51.957278207Z","close_reason":"SOUND audit: Fuse drops the inner stream on first None, prevents terminal repoll of the wrapped stream, and keeps size_hint aligned with fused exhaustion semantics.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.446","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:45:55.829089930Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.447","title":"[audit][net/dns] Deep audit src/net/dns/resolver.rs timeout + Happy Eyeballs semantics","description":"Fresh bounded audit child under asupersync-1qfd0. Scope: deeply inspect src/net/dns/resolver.rs for concrete correctness bugs in hostname validation, cache interaction, timeout behavior, blocking DNS/connect bridging, and Happy Eyeballs connection semantics. Fix any real defect found, add targeted regression tests, validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands for touched surfaces, and update audit tracking artifacts if the audit completes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"IvoryDog","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:47:43.121457218Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T04:08:53.413095942Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T04:08:53.412588529Z","close_reason":"Completed: validated DNS resolver timeout/connect fix in current HEAD","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","dns","net","resolver"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.447","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:47:43.121457218Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.448","title":"[audit][stream] Preserve WatchStream waiter registration across Pending polls","description":"Fresh audit child for current-tree regression in src/stream/watch_stream.rs. WatchStream::poll_next constructs a temporary watch::changed() future each poll. When that future returns Pending, dropping it immediately unregisters the receiver waiter in ChangedFuture::drop, so later sends may never wake the task. Fix by retaining pending wait state across polls (or otherwise preserving registration), add a focused regression test that proves a send after an initial Pending poll wakes/yields correctly, and validate with rch-backed cargo commands only.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:51:57.840958601Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T04:06:37.619517397Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T04:06:37.619168949Z","close_reason":"Completed: preserved WatchStream waiter registration across Pending polls and added wake regression coverage","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream","watch"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.448","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:51:57.840958601Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2732,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.448","author":"ubuntu","text":"Patched the current-tree WatchStream regression by adding Receiver::poll_changed in src/channel/watch.rs and switching src/stream/watch_stream.rs to use that non-owning poll path instead of creating a short-lived changed() future every poll. Added regression test watch_stream_pending_poll_retains_waiter_registration proving Pending -> send -> wake -> Ready(Some(_)). Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-swift-watchstream-test-v2 cargo test -p asupersync watch_stream_pending_poll_retains_waiter_registration -- --nocapture (pass; rch sync failed open to local due transient .beads recovery rsync issue, then test passed); rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-swift-watchstream-check-v2 cargo check --all-targets (pass); rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-swift-watchstream-clippy-v2 cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings (pass); rch exec -- cargo fmt --check still fails in unrelated active files src/net/dns/resolver.rs, src/net/tcp/stream.rs, src/runtime/obligation_table.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:06:37Z"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.449","title":"[audit][stream] Remove unnecessary Unpin bound from Scan","description":"Fresh-eyes audit/fix in src/stream/scan.rs. The Scan combinator currently requires S: Unpin in its Stream impl even though pin-projection allows polling a pinned inner stream without moving it. Remove the unnecessary bound so StreamExt::scan works with pinned !Unpin streams, add a focused regression using a PhantomPinned stream, and validate with rch-backed cargo test/check/fmt/clippy commands only.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:55:45.095113023Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T03:55:45.095113023Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.449","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:55:45.095113023Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.449","title":"[audit][stream] Remove unnecessary Unpin bound from Scan","description":"Fresh-eyes audit/fix in src/stream/scan.rs. The Scan combinator currently requires S: Unpin in its Stream impl even though pin-projection allows polling a pinned inner stream without moving it. Remove the unnecessary bound so StreamExt::scan works with pinned !Unpin streams, add a focused regression using a PhantomPinned stream, and validate with rch-backed cargo test/check/fmt/clippy commands only.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:55:45.095113023Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T04:14:04.811948439Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T04:14:04.810872510Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.449","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:55:45.095113023Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.45","title":"[audit][web][session] Expire unknown fixation cookies on read-only requests","description":"SessionMiddleware currently treats unknown-but-valid session IDs as fixation attempts, but for read-only requests it leaves the attacker-supplied cookie in place because no new session is persisted and no cookie expiration is emitted. Patch src/web/session.rs so unknown valid IDs are actively expired even when the handler does not mutate session state, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo check/clippy/test commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BrightMill","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T05:02:54.940225743Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:25.377119764Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:25.377119764Z","close_reason":"Fixed unknown fixation cookie expiry in SessionMiddleware; added read-only regression coverage. Validation: rch remote targeted test passed; rch remote cargo check -p asupersync --lib exposed pre-existing unresolved memmem import in src/http/h1/codec.rs; rch remote cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib passed; workspace cargo fmt --check is blocked by existing merge conflict markers in asupersync-tokio-compat/src/runtime.rs; rustfmt --check src/web/session.rs passed.","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:25.377072737Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","security","session","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.45","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:02:54.940225743Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.450","title":"[audit][cli] Detect progress color against stderr, not stdout","description":"Fresh bounded audit child on src/cli/progress.rs and, if needed for a shared helper, src/cli/output.rs. ProgressReporter writes human progress updates to stderr, but color auto-detection currently follows stdout terminal state via ColorChoice::auto_detect()/should_colorize(). That can suppress color when stderr is a TTY and stdout is piped, or emit ANSI escapes when stderr is redirected but stdout is interactive. Fix the stream-selection logic so progress color decisions follow the actual progress sink, add focused regression coverage for both mismatch directions, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands only.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SapphireStone","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:57:38.831563749Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T03:57:38.831563749Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cli","output","progress"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.450","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:57:38.831563749Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.450","title":"[audit][cli] Detect progress color against stderr, not stdout","description":"Fresh bounded audit child on src/cli/progress.rs and, if needed for a shared helper, src/cli/output.rs. ProgressReporter writes human progress updates to stderr, but color auto-detection currently follows stdout terminal state via ColorChoice::auto_detect()/should_colorize(). That can suppress color when stderr is a TTY and stdout is piped, or emit ANSI escapes when stderr is redirected but stdout is interactive. Fix the stream-selection logic so progress color decisions follow the actual progress sink, add focused regression coverage for both mismatch directions, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands only.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SapphireStone","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:57:38.831563749Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T04:13:59.178819316Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T04:13:59.178465428Z","close_reason":"Completed: progress color detection now follows the actual stderr sink; feature-enabled check and focused regressions passed, with repo-wide clippy still blocked by unrelated current-head warnings outside this slice.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cli","output","progress"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.450","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:57:38.831563749Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2734,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.450","author":"SapphireStone","text":"2026-03-26 SapphireStone: Fixed the CLI progress color-selection bug by making ProgressReporter track its own sink terminal state instead of inheriting stdout-oriented auto-detection. Added ColorChoice::auto_detect_for()/should_colorize_for() in src/cli/output.rs, threaded target_is_terminal through ProgressReporter in src/cli/progress.rs, and added feature-gated regressions for both mismatch directions plus the helper contract. Validation: rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/rch-target-sapphirestone-cli-feature-check cargo check -p asupersync --features cli --lib => PASS; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/rch-target-sapphirestone-cli-feature-test-progress cargo test -p asupersync --features cli --lib progress_reporter_auto_color -- --nocapture => PASS (2 tests); rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/rch-target-sapphirestone-cli-feature-test-output cargo test -p asupersync --features cli --lib color_choice_auto_follows_target_terminal_state -- --nocapture => PASS (1 test); rustfmt +nightly --edition 2024 --check src/cli/output.rs src/cli/progress.rs => PASS; git diff --check -- src/cli/output.rs src/cli/progress.rs => PASS. Repo-required clippy lane remains blocked by unrelated current-head warnings in src/net/tcp/stream.rs:306 and src/cli/doctor/mod.rs:6697,6702,6707,6712,6717,15582,15590,15599.","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:13:55Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.46","title":"[audit][web] Make standalone compress/security middleware respect case-insensitive public headers","description":"src/web/compress.rs and src/web/security.rs assume lowercase keys in public Request/Response header HashMaps, so mixed-case headers inserted directly through the public fields can bypass Accept-Encoding negotiation, duplicate security headers, or leave Server unstripped. Fix the standalone web modules to use case-insensitive header access/canonicalization, add focused regressions, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands on the touched surface.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CoralCompass","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:07:31.575656032Z","created_by":"EmeraldRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:27.263125980Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:27.263125980Z","close_reason":"Current tree already satisfies bead contract; case-insensitive header handling and regressions are already present","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:27.263105151Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","headers","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.46","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:07:31.575656032Z","created_by":"EmeraldRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2475,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.46","author":"CoralCompass","text":"Audit result: current tree already satisfies this bead.\n\nSource evidence:\n- Request-side lookup is already case-insensitive in `src/web/extract.rs:89` (`Request::header`) so direct mixed-case `Accept-Encoding` inserts are honored by `src/web/compress.rs:110`.\n- Response-side helpers already canonicalize and match case-insensitively in `src/web/response.rs:154` (`header_value`), `src/web/response.rs:173` (`set_header`), `src/web/response.rs:190` (`ensure_header`), and `src/web/response.rs:200` (`remove_header`).\n- Compression regressions already cover the mixed-case cases at `src/web/compress.rs:293`, `src/web/compress.rs:310`, and `src/web/compress.rs:328`.\n- Security-header regressions already cover the mixed-case cases at `src/web/security.rs:267` and `src/web/security.rs:344`.\n- Supporting response helper regressions exist at `src/web/response.rs:478` and `src/web/response.rs:490`.\n- File-local formatting check passed: `rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/web/compress.rs src/web/security.rs src/web/response.rs src/web/extract.rs`.\n\nConclusion: no code change required for this bead; the requested case-insensitive behavior and canonicalization regressions are already present.","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:45:02Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.47","title":"[audit][web] Give RequestTraceMiddleware a deterministic time getter","description":"RequestTraceMiddleware in src/web/middleware.rs still measures elapsed time with std::time::Instant::now() when populating its duration header, which makes observable middleware output depend on wall-clock timing. Add a custom time_getter path similar to the timeout/rate-limit middleware, thread it through RequestTraceMiddleware, add focused regression coverage proving duration headers can be driven without sleeping, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"DustyLark","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T05:28:57.439306825Z","created_by":"SilentEagle","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:24.376583516Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:24.376583516Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in src/web/middleware.rs and verified via rch cargo test --lib request_trace_ -- --nocapture (5 request_trace tests passed).","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:24.376560734Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.47","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:28:57.439306825Z","created_by":"SilentEagle","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.48","title":"[audit][service] Give DnsServiceDiscovery a deterministic time getter","description":"DnsServiceDiscovery currently rate-limits hostname re-resolution via std::time::Instant::now()/elapsed, so poll interval behavior depends on wall-clock time and cannot be driven deterministically in tests or virtual-time harnesses. Add a custom time_getter path similar to service timeout/rate-limit and web middleware, switch cooldown bookkeeping to asupersync::types::Time, add focused regressions that advance time without sleeping for both success and error cooldown paths, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FoggyGorge","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T18:51:48.719605897Z","created_by":"AmberSpruce","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.380497294Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.380497294Z","close_reason":"Implemented deterministic DNS discovery time getter and tests; remaining fmt/clippy/lib-test blockers are unrelated workspace-frontier errors","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:16.380436080Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","dns","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.48","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:51:48.719605897Z","created_by":"AmberSpruce","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2461,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.48","author":"FoggyGorge","text":"Implemented deterministic cooldown time plumbing in src/service/discover.rs by replacing Instant-based last_resolve bookkeeping with asupersync::types::Time, adding DnsDiscoveryConfig::with_time_getter/time_getter, and covering both success and failure cooldown paths with non-sleeping time-driven regressions. Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-amberspruce-check cargo check --all-targets => pass. rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-amberspruce-fmt cargo fmt --check => blocked by unrelated parse error in src/web/middleware.rs:317. rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-amberspruce-clippy cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings => blocked by unrelated redundant-clone lint in src/web/session.rs:997. rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-amberspruce-test2 cargo test --lib dns_discovery_time_getter => blocked by unrelated lib-test compile error in src/service/load_balance.rs:970 after I made the failure-path test deterministic using malformed host [::1 instead of external DNS behavior.","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:05:59Z"}]}
