 {"id":"asupersync-36m6p.1","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][E5] Deterministic profile-pack benchmark evidence bundle for throughput/latency deltas","description":"Generate a reproducible benchmark evidence bundle that compares auto/forced dual-kernel policy profile packs against sequential baseline on the GF256 dual-policy benchmark matrix, with explicit throughput and tail-latency deltas and fallback reasons. Update docs with exact rch commands and artifact pointers so E5 criterion #4 closure can be adjudicated from deterministic evidence.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"QuietDune","created_at":"2026-02-22T17:50:05.741132722Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-22T18:08:56.919174235Z","closed_at":"2026-02-22T18:08:56.919150221Z","close_reason":"Completed: deterministic profile-pack benchmark evidence packet delivered","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-36m6p.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-36m6p","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-22T17:50:05.741132722Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1980,"issue_id":"asupersync-36m6p.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"[2026-02-22 QuietDune] E5 profile-pack evidence packet completed.\n\nArtifacts created:\n- artifacts/raptorq_e5_profile_pack_benchmark_summary.md\n- artifacts/e5_profile_pack_auto_capture.log\n- artifacts/e5_profile_pack_sequential_capture.log\n- artifacts/e5_profile_pack_fused_capture.log\n\nDocs updated:\n- docs/raptorq_baseline_bench_profile.md (new E5 profile-pack capture section + repro bundle)\n\nExecution details (rch-only):\n- Ran `gf256_dual_policy` benchmark matrix in three modes (`auto`, `sequential`, `fused`) with identical sample/warmup/measurement settings.\n- Captures include deterministic probe metadata and throughput outputs for all six dual-policy scenarios.\n\nKey findings:\n1. All captures reported `kernel=Scalar`, `architecture_class=generic-scalar`, `profile_pack=scalar-conservative-v1`.\n2. `Auto` mode selected sequential decisions (as expected from scalar-conservative windows).\n3. Throughput deltas are mixed by scenario in scalar mode; no stable, material fused uplift across all scenarios.\n4. This packet strengthens E5 governance evidence, but SIMD-profile-pack uplift remains unproven on this host/build shape.\n\nSuggested next closure step:\n- rerun the same command bundle on a shape where SIMD kernels are active, then compare auto vs sequential vs forced-fused using the same scenario matrix.\n","created_at":"2026-02-22T18:07:17Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-36m6p.10","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][E5] Align gf256 unit fixtures with current x86 profile-pack contract","description":"Live Track-E x86 profile-pack metadata, docs, artifacts, and perf invariants now enforce the 2026-03-04 default contract (dual-mul auto disabled; addmul window 24576..32768 total bytes; addmul_min_lane 8192), but some lower-level unit fixtures in src/raptorq/gf256.rs still hard-code the older pre-refresh window values (mul 8192..24576, addmul 12288..16384, lane floor 2048). Scope: align those internal fixtures and assertions with the current x86 contract, keep focused decision-reason coverage truthful, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo gates for the touched surface.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GreenBrook","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-21T01:44:37.141058087Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T01:57:56.921215835Z","closed_at":"2026-03-21T01:57:56.921192822Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["gf256","raptorq","simd","tests"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-36m6p.10","depends_on_id":"asupersync-36m6p","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T01:44:37.141058087Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-36m6p.11","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][E5] Enforce target-environment metadata in dual-policy probe contract","description":"Fresh E5 validation hardening slice. benches/raptorq_benchmark.rs emits target_arch/target_os/target_env/target_endian/target_pointer_width_bits in dual-policy probe logs, but scripts/run_raptorq_e2e.sh::validate_dual_policy_probe_contract() and tests/raptorq_perf_invariants.rs::track_e_dual_policy_probe_contract_surface_tokens() do not require those fields. This patch now wires those five target-environment fields into both validator surfaces so the contract fails closed on lost architecture provenance. Validation in progress: local git diff check + bash -n passed; focused rch cargo test selector pending.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"HazyCrane","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-21T02:31:51.534387549Z","created_by":"HazyCrane","updated_at":"2026-03-21T02:54:34.966737339Z","closed_at":"2026-03-21T02:54:34.966714096Z","close_reason":"Fresh-eyes follow-up fixed the remaining Track-E probe-contract omission: the shell validator and perf-invariant test now require emitted kernel/manifest_schema_version/profile_schema_version fields in addition to the previously added target-environment bundle. Local diff/syntax/rustfmt checks passed; focused rch test selector passed again; rch cargo check --all-targets passed again.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["benchmarking","performance","raptorq","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-36m6p.11","depends_on_id":"asupersync-36m6p","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T02:31:51.534387549Z","created_by":"HazyCrane","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-36m6p.12","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][E5] Lock host-vs-profile architecture truth for supported profile-pack env requests","description":"The E5 GF256 profile-pack surface already exposes both host architecture class and active profile metadata, but the current regression coverage does not directly lock the supported env-request path where a SIMD-capable host intentionally selects the scalar profile pack. Add bounded coverage proving that this path preserves truthfulness: the host architecture class stays the detected host class, the active profile metadata stays scalar-conservative, the env-request bit remains visible, and canonical provenance is preserved when no numeric overrides or forced modes are present.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Unit coverage in src/raptorq/gf256.rs directly exercises a supported profile-pack env request and asserts host-vs-selected-profile architecture fields remain intentionally split. 2. Integration/perf-invariant coverage proves the live contract surfaces preserve the same truthfulness expectations at the bench/probe layer or equivalent manifest-backed surface. 3. Validation uses rch-backed targeted cargo lanes only. 4. The bead comment/mail trail records the exact files and validation commands used.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SageGorge","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-27T03:44:54.569322911Z","created_by":"SageGorge","updated_at":"2026-03-27T03:45:07.409988483Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["contract","gf256","raptorq","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-36m6p.12","depends_on_id":"asupersync-36m6p","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T03:44:54.569322911Z","created_by":"SageGorge","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
