+{"id":"asupersync-36m6p.13","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][E5] Require decision_evidence_status in dual-policy probe contract","description":"The Track-E bench/probe emitter already serializes `decision_evidence_status`, but the checked-in dual-policy probe contract currently does not require that field in either `scripts/run_raptorq_e2e.sh` or the corresponding invariant in `tests/raptorq_perf_invariants.rs`. Tighten the contract so the live validation surface explicitly fails if evidence-maturity metadata is dropped from probe records.","acceptance_criteria":"1. `scripts/run_raptorq_e2e.sh` dual-policy probe validation explicitly requires a non-empty `decision_evidence_status` field and checks the override branch keeps the override-specific evidence status. 2. `tests/raptorq_perf_invariants.rs` locks the same requirement so the checked-in invariant fails if the probe contract drops evidence-maturity metadata. 3. Validation uses rch-backed targeted cargo lanes only. 4. Bead comment and agent-mail thread record the touched files and exact validation commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SageGorge","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-27T04:12:58.164330220Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T04:18:08.981944391Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T04:18:08.981573722Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["contract","gf256","raptorq","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-36m6p.13","depends_on_id":"asupersync-36m6p","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:12:58.164330220Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2735,"issue_id":"asupersync-36m6p.13","author":"SageGorge","text":"Completed bounded Track-E probe-contract tightening for `decision_evidence_status`.\n\nFiles changed:\n- scripts/run_raptorq_e2e.sh\n- tests/raptorq_perf_invariants.rs\n\nWhat changed:\n- `validate_dual_policy_probe_contract` now requires a no